# Language: US English

- All identifiers (classes, functions, variables, packages), comments, commit
  messages, log strings, and documentation MUST be written in US English.
- Use US spelling: "color" not "colour", "behavior" not "behaviour",
  "synchronize" not "synchronise", "canceled" not "cancelled".
- This applies to all files in the repository, including Markdown docs.
